logic

Class CommandFacade

  • java.lang.Object
    • logic.CommandFacade

  • public class CommandFacade
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a facade pattern to parse the CommandObject that has been returned by the parser. A new CommandFacade class is initialised with each new user input, and all relevant arguments are passed to this class. The variables that will be actually used depends on the input of the user.
    Author:
    RuiBin, ChongYan

    • Method Detail

      • run

        public void run()
        The run method is called by Logic after each initialisation of the CommandFacade class. It parses the command type and calls the appropriate function. Responsible for manipulating the undoList and determining whether the redoList should be cleared.
        The redoList will be cleared as long as the command given is not an undo or redo.
        A "reverse" CommandObject will be created and pushed into the undoList if the current CommandObject is an action which manipulates the existing task list.
